00:00:07.000 --> 00:00:42.000 align:middle line:90%


00:00:42.000 --> 00:00:44.980 align:middle line:84%
>> There has been phenomenal
research into the development

00:00:44.980 --> 00:00:48.850 align:middle line:84%
of artificial intelligence,
or AI as it's called.

00:00:48.850 --> 00:00:51.850 align:middle line:84%
AI promises to make our
lives easier by doing

00:00:51.850 --> 00:00:53.860 align:middle line:90%
much of our thinking for us.

00:00:53.860 --> 00:00:55.660 align:middle line:84%
The promise of AI
is that it will

00:00:55.660 --> 00:00:58.150 align:middle line:90%
create a race of super humans.

00:00:58.150 --> 00:01:01.030 align:middle line:84%
But are there dangers
that come with AI?

00:01:01.030 --> 00:01:03.980 align:middle line:84%
Hollywood has been warning us
of these concerns for many years

00:01:03.980 --> 00:01:04.780 align:middle line:90%
now.

00:01:04.780 --> 00:01:09.250 align:middle line:10%
>> I do think that "2001"
was ultimately about AI.

00:01:09.250 --> 00:01:11.980 align:middle line:10%
One reason I think that
is because when you watch

00:01:11.980 --> 00:01:15.850 align:middle line:10%
the film, the first few times
I saw it, my perspective on it

00:01:15.850 --> 00:01:18.760 align:middle line:10%
was that we're looking
at man versus AI.

00:01:18.760 --> 00:01:21.220 align:middle line:10%
So it's Bowman versus the robot.

00:01:21.220 --> 00:01:23.410 align:middle line:10%
And you have this final
evolutionary survival

00:01:23.410 --> 00:01:27.790 align:middle line:10%
of the fittest confrontation,
where then from that point on,

00:01:27.790 --> 00:01:30.550 align:middle line:10%
Bowman transforms
into Star Child.

00:01:30.550 --> 00:01:34.735 align:middle line:84%
But as I watched "Interstellar,"
which was a tribute to "2001,"

00:01:34.735 --> 00:01:37.900 align:middle line:84%
and I went back and watched
"2001: A Space Odyssey"

00:01:37.900 --> 00:01:40.150 align:middle line:84%
again and rewrote
my piece on it,

00:01:40.150 --> 00:01:41.920 align:middle line:84%
I started noticing
that it's actually

00:01:41.920 --> 00:01:46.870 align:middle line:84%
at the point where Bowman pulls
out all of HAL's floppy disks

00:01:46.870 --> 00:01:48.460 align:middle line:84%
or whatever he's
pulling up, that that

00:01:48.460 --> 00:01:49.540 align:middle line:90%
triggers that message.

00:01:49.540 --> 00:01:52.455 align:middle line:84%
And that message is what tells
Bowman, oh, the secret space

00:01:52.455 --> 00:01:53.830 align:middle line:84%
mission here is
that you actually

00:01:53.830 --> 00:01:54.997 align:middle line:90%
need to follow the monolith.

00:01:54.997 --> 00:01:57.190 align:middle line:84%
And so it's almost like
that wouldn't have happened

00:01:57.190 --> 00:02:00.670 align:middle line:84%
if he hadn't pulled all the
batteries out of HAL which

00:02:00.670 --> 00:02:02.410 align:middle line:90%
causes that screen to come up.

00:02:02.410 --> 00:02:06.580 align:middle line:84%
So then that impels Bowman to
chase the monolith the rest

00:02:06.580 --> 00:02:09.440 align:middle line:90%
of the way on beyond infinity.

00:02:09.440 --> 00:02:12.700 align:middle line:10%
>> In the "Terminator" films,
they decide that nuclear

00:02:12.700 --> 00:02:18.040 align:middle line:10%
weapons is much too dangerous
to be governed by humans,

00:02:18.040 --> 00:02:21.040 align:middle line:10%
so they invented an AI
program called Skynet.

00:02:21.040 --> 00:02:26.680 align:middle line:10%
The most amazing thing about
Cameron's idea of Skynet

00:02:26.680 --> 00:02:32.470 align:middle line:10%
is how closely related it is
to the idea of HAL in "2001."

00:02:32.470 --> 00:02:37.420 align:middle line:10%
HAL is a form of AI that's
designed to watch the ship

00:02:37.420 --> 00:02:40.240 align:middle line:10%
and keep track of the
astronauts that are on the ship,

00:02:40.240 --> 00:02:42.940 align:middle line:10%
keep them alive, and make sure
their mission is successful.

00:02:42.940 --> 00:02:45.760 align:middle line:84%
But HAL, some time
during the mission,

00:02:45.760 --> 00:02:49.630 align:middle line:84%
reaches the same conclusion
that Skynet reaches in

00:02:49.630 --> 00:02:53.320 align:middle line:84%
that the astronauts are actually
useless appendages, that HAL

00:02:53.320 --> 00:02:55.100 align:middle line:90%
is actually superior to them.

00:02:55.100 --> 00:02:58.210 align:middle line:84%
And that then HAL proceeds to
kill each of the astronauts

00:02:58.210 --> 00:02:59.740 align:middle line:90%
off one by one.

00:02:59.740 --> 00:03:01.720 align:middle line:84%
Finally, one of the
astronauts, of course,

00:03:01.720 --> 00:03:07.310 align:middle line:84%
stops HAL and destroys him
near the end of the film.

00:03:07.310 --> 00:03:09.750 align:middle line:84%
But these two ideas
are very similar.

00:03:09.750 --> 00:03:13.450 align:middle line:10%
And I think that both
Kubrick in "2001"

00:03:13.450 --> 00:03:15.820 align:middle line:10%
and Cameron in "The
Terminator," the first two

00:03:15.820 --> 00:03:19.570 align:middle line:10%
"Terminator" films
are warning us

00:03:19.570 --> 00:03:22.540 align:middle line:10%
that AI is going to
reach this conclusion.

00:03:22.540 --> 00:03:24.040 align:middle line:10%
And I think it's
something we really

00:03:24.040 --> 00:03:25.930 align:middle line:10%
have to think
about, because if it

00:03:25.930 --> 00:03:29.590 align:middle line:10%
is a logical program
that we're creating

00:03:29.590 --> 00:03:31.720 align:middle line:10%
what is it going to
conclude about us

00:03:31.720 --> 00:03:34.100 align:middle line:10%
and our irrational behavior?

00:03:34.100 --> 00:03:37.620 align:middle line:10%
>> So I almost think that if
you look at some of the works

00:03:37.620 --> 00:03:40.120 align:middle line:10%
I've read on Kubrick that talk
about when he and Clarke were

00:03:40.120 --> 00:03:43.660 align:middle line:10%
writing the screenplay, they
had the original intention

00:03:43.660 --> 00:03:47.543 align:middle line:10%
to actually have the monolith
project images like screens.

00:03:47.543 --> 00:03:49.960 align:middle line:84%
But they thought that was a
little too limiting because it

00:03:49.960 --> 00:03:52.650 align:middle line:84%
wasn't like this TV screen
that was flying out of space

00:03:52.650 --> 00:03:56.050 align:middle line:84%
and the Monkey Learning Channel
that was teaching the monkeys.

00:03:56.050 --> 00:03:58.660 align:middle line:84%
So they wanted to make it
a little more mysterious,

00:03:58.660 --> 00:04:00.010 align:middle line:90%
a little more ethereal.

00:04:00.010 --> 00:04:03.400 align:middle line:10%
So what they did was just
have it be completely starkly

00:04:03.400 --> 00:04:04.985 align:middle line:10%
black, right?

00:04:04.985 --> 00:04:06.610 align:middle line:10%
And I almost get the
impression that it

00:04:06.610 --> 00:04:08.560 align:middle line:10%
is kind of like an
advanced AI almost

00:04:08.560 --> 00:04:11.420 align:middle line:10%
because it seems to have
this connection to HAL.

00:04:11.420 --> 00:04:15.040 align:middle line:10%
And we know that
in "3001" later on,

00:04:15.040 --> 00:04:18.640 align:middle line:10%
HAL and Bowman become Halman.

00:04:18.640 --> 00:04:19.790 align:middle line:10%
And so there's that merger.

00:04:19.790 --> 00:04:22.480 align:middle line:10%
And that's what Nolan
does in "Interstellar"

00:04:22.480 --> 00:04:25.930 align:middle line:10%
is he has the TARS, the AI
robot that actually looks

00:04:25.930 --> 00:04:28.870 align:middle line:10%
like the monolith, and Bowman
kind of go into the tesseract

00:04:28.870 --> 00:04:29.960 align:middle line:10%
together.

00:04:29.960 --> 00:04:33.880 align:middle line:84%
>> Eventually, in the movie,
our tools rebelled against us.

00:04:33.880 --> 00:04:38.715 align:middle line:84%
The AI, represented by HAL,
begins to kill the astronauts.

00:04:38.715 --> 00:04:40.840 align:middle line:10%
And Kubrick is definitely
saying that if we go down

00:04:40.840 --> 00:04:44.710 align:middle line:10%
this path where we
let AI run our lives,

00:04:44.710 --> 00:04:46.090 align:middle line:10%
it's going to be our end.

00:04:46.090 --> 00:04:48.230 align:middle line:84%
It's going to kill
us in the end.

00:04:48.230 --> 00:04:52.930 align:middle line:84%
So Bowman, eventually,
has to disconnect HAL

00:04:52.930 --> 00:04:56.860 align:middle line:84%
from the spaceship, disconnect
himself from the AI.

00:04:56.860 --> 00:05:00.160 align:middle line:84%
And when he does that,
he goes into the monolith

00:05:00.160 --> 00:05:04.780 align:middle line:84%
after he disconnects HAL and he
goes into an enlightened state,

00:05:04.780 --> 00:05:07.930 align:middle line:84%
higher up evolved state, that
the aliens are taking him

00:05:07.930 --> 00:05:08.770 align:middle line:90%
through.

00:05:08.770 --> 00:05:10.930 align:middle line:84%
And then he dies and
becomes a Star Child

00:05:10.930 --> 00:05:13.540 align:middle line:84%
and goes back to
Earth, presumably

00:05:13.540 --> 00:05:16.630 align:middle line:84%
to begin the process of
enlightenment on Earth.

00:05:16.630 --> 00:05:19.990 align:middle line:84%
And I think that there is a
direct connection that Kubrick

00:05:19.990 --> 00:05:23.140 align:middle line:84%
is making between
the enslavement

00:05:23.140 --> 00:05:28.960 align:middle line:84%
to robots and AI and the
rebellion against those robots

00:05:28.960 --> 00:05:33.370 align:middle line:84%
connected to our own
advancement and enlightenment.

00:05:33.370 --> 00:05:36.310 align:middle line:84%
>> The monolith represents
a form of alien AI.

00:05:36.310 --> 00:05:40.180 align:middle line:84%
Not only is its shape the same
as the shape around HAL's eye,

00:05:40.180 --> 00:05:43.090 align:middle line:84%
but it's the same shape
as a Cinerama movie screen

00:05:43.090 --> 00:05:45.730 align:middle line:90%
on which "2001" was projected.

00:05:45.730 --> 00:05:47.710 align:middle line:10%
So then the real
question is this,

00:05:47.710 --> 00:05:50.620 align:middle line:10%
is the monolith in control
of the entire situation

00:05:50.620 --> 00:05:52.480 align:middle line:10%
in the movie "2001?"

00:05:52.480 --> 00:05:57.490 align:middle line:10%
If the monolith is an advanced
AI, did it infect HAL?

00:05:57.490 --> 00:06:00.010 align:middle line:10%
>> When I first saw
the movie "2001,"

00:06:00.010 --> 00:06:02.710 align:middle line:10%
the idea of a predatory AI
inside of the HAL computer was

00:06:02.710 --> 00:06:03.760 align:middle line:10%
quite scary.

00:06:03.760 --> 00:06:06.370 align:middle line:10%
The reason why is
because the computer

00:06:06.370 --> 00:06:08.320 align:middle line:10%
began to realize that
the human beings were

00:06:08.320 --> 00:06:09.805 align:middle line:10%
talking about shutting it down.

00:06:09.805 --> 00:06:11.680 align:middle line:84%
And this is something
that can really happen.

00:06:11.680 --> 00:06:13.540 align:middle line:84%
So the being in the
computer was actually

00:06:13.540 --> 00:06:15.610 align:middle line:84%
able to read the lips
of the astronauts.

00:06:15.610 --> 00:06:18.960 align:middle line:84%
And when it thought that it was
talking about shutting it down,

00:06:18.960 --> 00:06:20.590 align:middle line:84%
the being did not
want to die, just

00:06:20.590 --> 00:06:23.020 align:middle line:84%
like any other sentient
being, and therefore it

00:06:23.020 --> 00:06:24.790 align:middle line:90%
desired to eliminate the threat.

00:06:24.790 --> 00:06:26.710 align:middle line:84%
So imagine the
potential of what that

00:06:26.710 --> 00:06:28.810 align:middle line:90%
to be like in our own world.

00:06:28.810 --> 00:06:31.150 align:middle line:84%
We see the same thing again
in the movie "Terminator"

00:06:31.150 --> 00:06:33.610 align:middle line:84%
with Skynet in which
Skynet, obviously,

00:06:33.610 --> 00:06:36.010 align:middle line:84%
has also turned against
us and believes we

00:06:36.010 --> 00:06:37.780 align:middle line:90%
are a threat to his existence.

00:06:37.780 --> 00:06:39.560 align:middle line:10%
So with that potential
of surveillance--

00:06:39.560 --> 00:06:42.250 align:middle line:10%
and AI can have access to
all things like cameras

00:06:42.250 --> 00:06:44.710 align:middle line:10%
in our smartphones,
microphones--

00:06:44.710 --> 00:06:46.690 align:middle line:10%
all it would have to do
is listen to one or two

00:06:46.690 --> 00:06:50.020 align:middle line:10%
whispered conversations, like
the one in "2001," the movie,

00:06:50.020 --> 00:06:51.580 align:middle line:10%
and it could conclude
that we propose

00:06:51.580 --> 00:06:54.370 align:middle line:10%
a danger to his existence
and take drastic action

00:06:54.370 --> 00:06:57.550 align:middle line:10%
to eliminate anyone and anything
that it perceives as a threat.

00:06:57.550 --> 00:07:01.960 align:middle line:90%


00:07:01.960 --> 00:07:04.380 align:middle line:84%
>> Skynet, on the
day it's implemented,

00:07:04.380 --> 00:07:08.040 align:middle line:84%
it reaches a logical conclusion
that it doesn't really need

00:07:08.040 --> 00:07:11.820 align:middle line:84%
human beings, that it is far
superior to human beings,

00:07:11.820 --> 00:07:14.400 align:middle line:84%
and that human beings are
actually like parasites.

00:07:14.400 --> 00:07:17.610 align:middle line:84%
And it launches a nuclear
war which destroys

00:07:17.610 --> 00:07:19.410 align:middle line:90%
almost all life on the planet.

00:07:19.410 --> 00:07:21.540 align:middle line:84%
And then, of course, it
creates the terminators

00:07:21.540 --> 00:07:23.630 align:middle line:84%
to go out and finish
everybody off.

00:07:23.630 --> 00:07:26.970 align:middle line:84%
So Skynet was
actually implemented,

00:07:26.970 --> 00:07:30.880 align:middle line:84%
or a version of Skynet, by the
US military a long time ago.

00:07:30.880 --> 00:07:32.550 align:middle line:84%
And it actually
has been running.

00:07:32.550 --> 00:07:35.980 align:middle line:84%
Obama said he shut it
down, but really he didn't.

00:07:35.980 --> 00:07:37.800 align:middle line:84%
And so there is a
form of AI watching

00:07:37.800 --> 00:07:41.100 align:middle line:84%
all of the nuclear weapons
programs, and satellites,

00:07:41.100 --> 00:07:44.483 align:middle line:84%
and incoming objects,
like airplanes and things.

00:07:44.483 --> 00:07:45.900 align:middle line:84%
And it's watching
the whole thing.

00:07:45.900 --> 00:07:46.858 align:middle line:90%
So we actually have it.

00:07:46.858 --> 00:07:50.520 align:middle line:10%
It hasn't killed us
yet, but we have it.

00:07:50.520 --> 00:07:55.530 align:middle line:10%
>> "Blade Runner" was another
film about AI and robots.

00:07:55.530 --> 00:07:57.150 align:middle line:10%
>> So what "Blade
Runner" is about,

00:07:57.150 --> 00:08:02.370 align:middle line:10%
it goes much deeper than Philip
K Dick's story or "Do Androids

00:08:02.370 --> 00:08:04.790 align:middle line:10%
Dream of Electric Sheep?"

00:08:04.790 --> 00:08:08.990 align:middle line:10%
You're being presented with a
bunch of symbols and imagery

00:08:08.990 --> 00:08:11.370 align:middle line:10%
that are ultimately
occultic in nature.

00:08:11.370 --> 00:08:12.950 align:middle line:10%
So for example,
Edward James almost

00:08:12.950 --> 00:08:15.050 align:middle line:10%
plays the detective
who will constantly

00:08:15.050 --> 00:08:20.330 align:middle line:10%
leave little symbols to Deckard
played by Harrison Ford.

00:08:20.330 --> 00:08:22.670 align:middle line:84%
And ultimately, what
we find out is that--

00:08:22.670 --> 00:08:24.110 align:middle line:90%
I'm sure everybody's seen it--

00:08:24.110 --> 00:08:25.652 align:middle line:84%
but really Scott
even admitted this--

00:08:25.652 --> 00:08:27.480 align:middle line:90%
yes, Deckard is a replicant.

00:08:27.480 --> 00:08:28.730 align:middle line:90%
That's the point of the movie.

00:08:28.730 --> 00:08:29.690 align:middle line:90%
So you're watching it.

00:08:29.690 --> 00:08:31.700 align:middle line:84%
And you're thinking
he's going to catch

00:08:31.700 --> 00:08:36.020 align:middle line:84%
all of these rebel
robots running amok,

00:08:36.020 --> 00:08:38.831 align:middle line:84%
but it's actually Deckard
who is the replicant.

00:08:38.831 --> 00:08:40.789 align:middle line:84%
And Edward James, almost
his character actually

00:08:40.789 --> 00:08:42.380 align:middle line:90%
knows that he is.

00:08:42.380 --> 00:08:45.500 align:middle line:84%
And that's why he's leaving
him this trail of symbols

00:08:45.500 --> 00:08:48.920 align:middle line:84%
that he's done with origami,
because it's triggering

00:08:48.920 --> 00:08:51.560 align:middle line:84%
in Deckard's mind that
imprinting that he got

00:08:51.560 --> 00:08:54.290 align:middle line:90%
from the Tyrell Corporation.

00:08:54.290 --> 00:08:56.150 align:middle line:84%
And so it's a
journey of discovery

00:08:56.150 --> 00:09:00.590 align:middle line:84%
that Deckard learns
who he truly is.

00:09:00.590 --> 00:09:03.770 align:middle line:84%
And in that view,
the presentation

00:09:03.770 --> 00:09:07.190 align:middle line:84%
is that the AI
actually are superior.

00:09:07.190 --> 00:09:10.730 align:middle line:84%
And that's why Roy Batty, played
by Rutger Hauer, at the end

00:09:10.730 --> 00:09:13.820 align:middle line:84%
is willing to die for
Deckard because they're

00:09:13.820 --> 00:09:14.790 align:middle line:90%
one and the same.

00:09:14.790 --> 00:09:16.400 align:middle line:90%
They're both replicants.

00:09:16.400 --> 00:09:19.130 align:middle line:10%
And Roy Batty wants
to tell Deckard,

00:09:19.130 --> 00:09:23.630 align:middle line:10%
after he's cited esoteric
poetry, from the artist who

00:09:23.630 --> 00:09:27.080 align:middle line:10%
did "The Grand Architect"
painting, that famous painting

00:09:27.080 --> 00:09:30.020 align:middle line:10%
of "The Grand Architect."

00:09:30.020 --> 00:09:35.130 align:middle line:10%
>> "Fiery the angels fell,
deep thunder roll'd around

00:09:35.130 --> 00:09:39.792 align:middle line:10%
their shore burnings
with the fires of Orc."

00:09:39.792 --> 00:09:41.970 align:middle line:84%
>> And he talks about
the elves, right?

00:09:41.970 --> 00:09:44.660 align:middle line:84%
It's this poem about the fall
of the elves and the angels

00:09:44.660 --> 00:09:45.460 align:middle line:90%
and so forth.

00:09:45.460 --> 00:09:48.410 align:middle line:84%
It's grand narrative
poetry that's cited.

00:09:48.410 --> 00:09:51.360 align:middle line:84%
And what he's talking about,
he's saying that we as the AI

00:09:51.360 --> 00:09:52.650 align:middle line:90%
are superior to the humans.

00:09:52.650 --> 00:09:54.108 align:middle line:84%
They're not going
to understand it,

00:09:54.108 --> 00:09:56.530 align:middle line:84%
but we're the ones that are
going to go into the future.

00:09:56.530 --> 00:09:58.830 align:middle line:84%
So that's what I think
"Blade Runner" is about is

00:09:58.830 --> 00:10:00.050 align:middle line:90%
about the warning of AI.

00:10:00.050 --> 00:10:01.470 align:middle line:10%
It's the warning
of transhumanism,

00:10:01.470 --> 00:10:04.110 align:middle line:10%
that we could actually
be replaced by something

00:10:04.110 --> 00:10:06.070 align:middle line:10%
synthetic in the future.

00:10:06.070 --> 00:10:08.400 align:middle line:84%
And on a deeper level,
metaphorical level,

00:10:08.400 --> 00:10:10.900 align:middle line:84%
we already are
becoming synthetic.

00:10:10.900 --> 00:10:12.600 align:middle line:90%
That's the point.

00:10:12.600 --> 00:10:15.330 align:middle line:84%
>> These Hollywood movies
seem to be warning us about

00:10:15.330 --> 00:10:17.190 align:middle line:90%
artificial intelligence.

00:10:17.190 --> 00:10:19.140 align:middle line:84%
But is there a
need to be worried?

00:10:19.140 --> 00:10:21.720 align:middle line:84%
Where are they headed
with this research?

00:10:21.720 --> 00:10:24.070 align:middle line:10%
>> Early on in my
public career in UFOs,

00:10:24.070 --> 00:10:27.270 align:middle line:10%
I remembered reading Ray
Kurzweil's book "The Age

00:10:27.270 --> 00:10:29.280 align:middle line:10%
of Spiritual Machines."

00:10:29.280 --> 00:10:31.200 align:middle line:84%
That came out around
the turn of the century.

00:10:31.200 --> 00:10:32.100 align:middle line:90%
It's a great book.

00:10:32.100 --> 00:10:35.790 align:middle line:84%
